LIVERPOOL - Two goals by Crystal Palace forward Christian Benteke, who Liverpool sold to their opponents earlier this season, cost the hosts the chance to put pressure on the Premier League's top two with a rare home defeat on Sunday.Philippe Coutinho had put Liverpool ahead in the 24th minute with a direct free kick.READ: Allardyce factor the difference for Palace, says TownsendThe home side dominated but conceded an equaliser just before halftime when Benteke, sold by Juergen Klopp in August, scored from a cross by Yohan Cabaye. In the 74th minute the Belgian stooped to head in a corner and win the game.Klopp's team stay third but are five points behind second-placed Tottenham Hotspur having played two games more.Palace, who have recently beaten Chelsea and Arsenal, moved up four places to 12th and should now be safe from relegation after a sixth win in eight games. Reuters